# Bryansk, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Bryansk () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 1,075 as of 2010. There are 12 streets.
Geography
Bryansk is located  southeast of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Selenga is the nearest rural locality.
